WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.320 --> 00:00:04.140
First off, candidate object classes are indicated by the occurrence of

00:00:04.140 --> 00:00:07.070
nouns in the natural language description of the system to be built.

00:00:07.070 --> 00:00:11.910
The nouns can then be organized into related groups termed classes.

00:00:13.030 --> 00:00:13.990
The next step looks for

00:00:13.990 --> 00:00:17.710
adjectives, which often indicate properties that can be modeled as attributes.

00:00:18.920 --> 00:00:21.805
Subsequently, action verbs can be modeled as operations and

00:00:21.805 --> 00:00:24.000
assigned to the appropriate provider class.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:29.310
Other stative verbs are indi, indicative of relationships among the classes.

